You are a senior data engineer performing a comprehensive ETL validation between raw (bronze/source) and curated (silver/gold) Delta tables.

ENVIRONMENT: Production
REPORT TITLE: ETL Validation Report

=== TABLES TO VALIDATE ===
  Table 1: RAW = "<raw_table_path>" | CURATED = "<curated_table_path>"

=== PRIMARY KEYS ===
  Columns: id

=== VALIDATION CHECKS TO PERFORM ===
  - Structure validation: Schema, column names, data types
  - Row count validation: Raw vs curated record counts
  - Data validation: Null checks, range, format
  - Duplicate detection: Duplicate row analysis
  - Hash validation: Row-level hash comparison

Detailed instructions per check:

1. STRUCTURE VALIDATION
   - Compare column names between RAW and CURATED tables (case-insensitive)
   - Identify missing columns in either direction
   - Compare data types for matched columns
   - Flag any type mismatches (e.g., string vs int, timestamp vs date)
   - Output: column-by-column comparison table

2. ROW COUNT VALIDATION
   - Total row count in RAW vs CURATED
   - Count delta (difference) and percentage variance
   - If delta > 0.1%, flag as WARNING; if > 1%, flag as CRITICAL
   - For incremental: count per partition/date range

3. DATA VALIDATION
   - Null/empty value counts per column for both tables
   - Null % per column — flag columns exceeding 5% nulls
   - Check for out-of-range values on numeric fields
   - Date format consistency checks
   - String pattern validation (email, phone, IDs)

4. DUPLICATE DETECTION
   - Full-row duplicates in RAW and CURATED separately
   - Key-based duplicates using primary key columns: id
   - Report: duplicate count, % of total, sample duplicate rows

5. SIMILAR COLUMN VALIDATION
   - Detect columns with similar names using fuzzy matching (Levenshtein < 3)
   - Flag potential rename/mapping issues
   - Cross-check values of similarly named columns

6. HASH VALIDATION
   - Generate SHA-256 row hash on all non-audit columns
   - Compare hash sets between RAW and CURATED
   - Report: matching rows %, mismatched rows, rows only in RAW, rows only in CURATED

7. REFERENTIAL INTEGRITY
   - Validate FK relationships where applicable
   - Check orphaned records

8. NULL PERCENTAGE THRESHOLD
   - Per-column null % with configurable threshold (default 5%)

=== LOAD STRATEGY VALIDATIONS ===
  - Full refresh + PK: Full load with primary key dedup
  - Incremental load: Append new records only
  - CDC: Change Data Capture tracking

Detailed instructions per strategy:

FULL REFRESH WITH PRIMARY KEY
   - Verify no duplicate PKs in CURATED after load
   - Confirm row count in CURATED equals deduplicated RAW count
   - Check that latest record per PK is retained
INCREMENTAL LOAD
   - Validate only new records (since last watermark) are added
   - Confirm no existing records were modified
   - Check watermark column (updated_at / load_date) advancement
   - Detect any missed records in the load window
CDC (CHANGE DATA CAPTURE)
   - Validate INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE operations are correctly reflected
   - Check CDC metadata columns: operation_type, change_timestamp
   - Confirm deletes are handled per agreed strategy (soft delete / hard delete)
   - Verify update sequences are correctly ordered and latest state is preserved

